The paper discusses methods and models for swarm intelligence, which is a subfield of multi-agent systems (MAS) and robotics (RO). The abstract model of swarm performance and the abstract model of collective decision making are both relevant to MAS and can be applied to various types of swarms, including artificial and natural swarms. Therefore, cs.MA and cs.SY are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the calculation of key features of swarms, which involves algorithms and computational methods, making cs.AI a likely sub-category as well. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of Markov processes and probability calculations, which are relevant to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on swarm performance and robustness makes cs.RO a possible sub-category.
